content.description:
If passed, this governance proposal will do two things:

1. Increase the slashing penalty for downtime from 0.01% to 0.50%
2. Decrease the window 

If this proposal passes, validators must sign at least 5% of 5,000 blocks, which is 250 blocks. That means that a validator that misses 4,750 consecutive blocks will be considered by the system to have committed a liveness violation, where previously 9,500 consecutive blocks would need to have been missed to violate these system rules. Assuming 7s block times, validators offline for approximately 9.25 consecutive hours (instead of ~18.5 hours) will be slashed 0.5% (instead of 0.01%).
content.title: Slashing Parameter changes for validator downtime (Upgrade Test)

content.description:
If passed, this governance proposal will do the following thing:

Increase the window 

If this proposal passes, validators must sign at least 50% of 40,000 blocks, which is 20,000 blocks. That means that a validator that misses 20,000 consecutive blocks will be considered by the system to have committed a liveness violation, where previously 50 consecutive blocks would need to have been missed to violate these system rules. Assuming 1.37s block times, validators offline for approximately 7.61 consecutive hours (instead of 68.5s) will be slashed 1% and jailed at least 10 min
content.title: Slashing Parameter changes for validator downtime
